tasks.description:
Fix the chat system so messages display the sender's actual nickname instead of the hardcoded "unknow" placeholder.

**Modify: `js/chat.js`** — Update `addmessagetochat()` to parse and display sender nickname
**Modify: `server.js`** — Update chat message broadcast to include sender nickname
**Modify: `js/aks.js`** — Update MN handler to pass nickname to chat

**What to change:**

1. **`server.js` — chat message handling:**
   - On receiving `MN{text}` from a client:
     - Look up the sender's player object to get their nickname
     - Broadcast to ALL clients (including sender): `MN{senderNickname}|{messageText}`
     - The `|` separates nickname from message text

2. **`js/aks.js` — update MN handler:**
   - Currently at line 108: `addmessagetochat(received_msg.substring(2));`
   - Change to parse nickname and text:
     ```js
     case "N":
       var chatData = received_msg.substring(2);
       var separatorIdx = chatData.indexOf('|');
       var senderNick = chatData.substring(0, separatorIdx);
       var chatText = chatData.substring(separatorIdx + 1);
       addmessagetochat(senderNick, chatText);
     break;
     ```

3. **`js/chat.js` — update `addmessagetochat(nickname, data)`:**
   - Change function signature from `addmessagetochat(data)` to `addmessagetochat(nickname, data)`
   - Replace the hardcoded "unknow" with the `nickname` parameter:
     ```js
     var addmessagetochat = function(nickname, data) {
       var elem = document.createElement("li");
       elem.setAttribute("class", "ng-scope");
       elem.innerHTML = '<span><b class="nickname ng-binding">' + escapeHtml(nickname) + '</b>'
         + ':</span><span class="text">'
         + '<span class="ng-binding ng-scope">' + escapeHtml(data) + '</span>'
         + '</span>';
       var chat = document.getElementById("endchat");
       var parentdiv = chat.parentNode;
       parentdiv.insertBefore(elem, chat);
       // Auto-scroll to bottom
       var chatList = document.getElementById("listChat");
       chatList.scrollTop = chatList.scrollHeight;
     };
     ```
   - Add `escapeHtml` helper at the top of chat.js to prevent XSS:
     ```js
     function escapeHtml(str) {
       var div = document.createElement('div');
       div.textContent = str;
       return div.innerHTML;
     }
     ```

4. **Highlight own messages:**
   - Compare `nickname` with `playerNickname` (global from lobby)
   - If it matches, add class `my-msg` to the `<b>` tag for CSS styling

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Chat messages show sender's actual nickname (e.g., "Bob: hello everyone")
- No more "unknow" placeholder
- Own messages highlighted with `my-msg` class
- HTML entities properly escaped (XSS prevention)
- Chat auto-scrolls to latest message

Add a connection state overlay/toast that appears when the WebSocket connection is lost. Shows reconnect status with attempt count, updates when restored, shows permanent failure after max retries.

**Create: `js/connection-status.js`** — Connection state manager
**Create: `css/connection-status.css`** — Styles for the overlay/toast
**Modify: `index.html`** — Add HTML and script/link tags
**Modify: `js/aks.js`** — Integrate connection state tracking

**What to build:**

1. **HTML** (add to `index.html`):
```html
<div id="connection-overlay" style="display:none;">
  <div class="connection-toast">
    <div class="connection-icon" id="connection-icon">&#x26A0;</div>
    <div class="connection-text" id="connection-text">Connection lost</div>
    <div class="connection-detail" id="connection-detail">Reconnecting...</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

2. **`js/connection-status.js`** — ConnectionStatus manager:
```js
var ConnectionStatus = {
  maxRetries: 10,
  currentRetry: 0,
  isConnected: false,
  overlay: null,

  init: function() {
    this.overlay = document.getElementById('connection-overlay');
  },

  onConnected: function() {
    this.isConnected = true;
    this.currentRetry = 0;
    if (this.overlay.style.display !== 'none') {
      // Show "Reconnected!" briefly, then hide
      document.getElementById('connection-icon').innerHTML = '&#x2714;';
      document.getElementById('connection-text').textContent = 'Reconnected!';
      document.getElementById('connection-detail').textContent = '';
      this.overlay.classList.add('success');
      var self = this;
      setTimeout(function() {
        self.overlay.style.display = 'none';
        self.overlay.classList.remove('success');
      }, 2000);
    }
  },

  onDisconnected: function() {
    this.isConnected = false;
    this.overlay.style.display = 'flex';
    this.overlay.classList.remove('success');
    document.getElementById('connection-icon').innerHTML = '&#x26A0;';
    document.getElementById('connection-text').textContent = 'Connection lost';
    this.updateRetryInfo();
  },

  onRetrying: function(attempt) {
    this.currentRetry = attempt;
    this.updateRetryInfo();
  },

  updateRetryInfo: function() {
    if (this.currentRetry >= this.maxRetries) {
      document.getElementById('connection-detail').textContent = 'Failed to reconnect. Please refresh the page.';
      document.getElementById('connection-icon').innerHTML = '&#x2716;';
      this.overlay.classList.add('failed');
    } else {
      document.getElementById('connection-detail').textContent = 
        'Reconnecting... (attempt ' + (this.currentRetry + 1) + '/' + this.maxRetries + ')';
    }
  },

  onPermanentFailure: function() {
    document.getElementById('connection-detail').textContent = 'Failed to reconnect. Please refresh the page.';
    document.getElementById('connection-icon').innerHTML = '&#x2716;';
    this.overlay.classList.add('failed');
  }
};
```

3. **Modify `js/aks.js` — `InitializeSocket()`:**
   - Add retry counter: `var reconnectAttempt = 0;`
   - In `socket.onopen`: call `ConnectionStatus.onConnected();` and reset `reconnectAttempt = 0;`
   - In `socket.onclose`: call `ConnectionStatus.onDisconnected();` then on each retry call `ConnectionStatus.onRetrying(reconnectAttempt++);`
   - After `maxRetries` (10) attempts: stop retrying, call `ConnectionStatus.onPermanentFailure();`
   - Current behavior: `setTimeout(InitializeSocket, 1000)` with no limit — add retry logic:
     ```js
     socket.onclose = function() {
       if (reconnectAttempt < ConnectionStatus.maxRetries) {
         ConnectionStatus.onDisconnected();
         ConnectionStatus.onRetrying(reconnectAttempt);
         reconnectAttempt++;
         setTimeout(InitializeSocket, 2000);
       } else {
         ConnectionStatus.onPermanentFailure();
       }
     };
     ```

4. **CSS (`css/connection-status.css`):**
   - Overlay: position fixed, top 0, left 0, 100vw × 100vh, background rgba(0,0,0,0.6), z-index 9999, display flex, center content
   - Toast: background #333, padding 24px 32px, border-radius 12px, text-align center, min-width 320px
   - Icon: font-size 48px, color #ff9800 (warning orange)
   - Text: white, 18px, font-weight 600
   - Detail: #aaa, 14px, margin-top 8px
   - `.success` state: icon color #4CAF50 (green)
   - `.failed` state: icon color #f44336 (red)
   - Subtle fade-in animation on overlay appear

**Acceptance criteria:**
- When WebSocket disconnects, overlay appears immediately with warning icon
- Shows "Reconnecting... (attempt 1/10)" and increments
- On successful reconnect: shows green checkmark "Reconnected!" for 2s, then hides
- After 10 failed attempts: shows red X "Failed to reconnect. Please refresh the page."
- Does NOT show on initial connection (only on disconnect after being connected)

Implement the map regeneration and full round reset logic in `server.js`. This completes the round lifecycle.

**Implement `resetRound()` function (or finalize it from task-1):**

1. **Clear all active bombs:**
```
for (const b of bombs) {
  if (b.timer) clearTimeout(b.timer);
}
bombs.length = 0;
```

2. **Clear all active items:**
```
for (const item of items) {
  if (item.timer) clearTimeout(item.timer);
}
items.length = 0;
```

3. **Regenerate the map:**
```
cells.length = 0;
initializeMap(); // re-populates cells array
```

4. **Reset all players for new round:**
```
for (const [ws, player] of players) {
  player.alive = true;
  player.kills = 0;
  player.deaths = 0;
  player.speed = DEFAULT_SPEED;
  player.range = DEFAULT_RANGE;
  player.maxBombs = DEFAULT_MAX_BOMBS;
  player.bombCounter = 0;
  player.dir = 0;
  player.olddir = 2;
  player.onmove = false;
  // Respawn at random walkable position
  const spawnCell = getRandomWalkableCellStart();
  player.x = (spawnCell.x * TILE_SIZE) - 5;
  player.y = (spawnCell.y * TILE_SIZE) + 10;
}
```

5. **Broadcast new map to all clients:**
- Send `RR` to all (tells clients to prepare for map reload)
- Then send `WL{width}|{height}|{mapData}` to each client
- Then send entity data (each player's PA message) to each client

6. **Set round state to 'waiting':**
- `roundState.state = 'waiting';`
- If `players.size >= MIN_PLAYERS_TO_START`, auto-call `startRound()` after a short delay (e.g., 2 seconds)

**Modify existing `initializeMap()`** — ensure it clears the cells array first (it currently just pushes, so if called again it would double). Add `cells.length = 0;` at the start of `initializeMap()` if not already there.

**Files:** server.js
**Depends on:** task-1 (round state machine), task-2 (kill tracking fields)

Modify `js/aks.js` and `js/globals.js` to handle all new Sprint 2 protocol messages.

**Add to `js/globals.js`:**
```
// Round state
var roundState = 'waiting'; // 'waiting' | 'active' | 'ended'
var roundTimeRemaining = 0;
var roundWinner = null; // { id, nickname }
var roundResults = []; // [{ id, nickname, kills, deaths }, ...]

// Scoreboard
var scoreboardData = []; // [{ id, nickname, kills, deaths }, ...]

// Kill feed
var killFeed = []; // [{ killerId, killerNick, victimId, victimNick, time }, ...]
```

**Add to `js/aks.js` socket.onmessage switch — add new case 'R' (round messages):**
```
case "R":
  switch (action) {
    case "S": // Round state: RS{state}|{timeRemainingMs}
      var parts = received_msg.substring(2).split("|");
      roundState = parts[0];
      roundTimeRemaining = Number(parts[1]);
      if (typeof HUD !== 'undefined') HUD.updateRoundState(roundState, roundTimeRemaining);
      break;
    case "W": // Round winner: RW{winnerId}|{winnerNickname}
      var parts = received_msg.substring(2).split("|");
      roundWinner = { id: Number(parts[0]), nickname: parts[1] };
      break;
    case "R": // Round reset: RR
      // Clear local state, prepare for new map
      if (typeof HUD !== 'undefined') HUD.hideResults();
      roundWinner = null;
      roundResults = [];
      killFeed = [];
      break;
    case "E": // Round end results: RE{winnerId}|{winnerNick}|{id}|{nick}|{kills}|{deaths};...
      var data = received_msg.substring(2);
      var playerEntries = data.split(";");
      var firstEntry = playerEntries[0].split("|");
      roundWinner = { id: Number(firstEntry[0]), nickname: firstEntry[1] };
      roundResults = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < playerEntries.length; i++) {
        var p = playerEntries[i].split("|");
        if (p.length >= 6) {
          roundResults.push({ id: Number(p[2]), nickname: p[3], kills: Number(p[4]), deaths: Number(p[5]) });
        }
      }
      if (typeof HUD !== 'undefined') HUD.showResults(roundWinner, roundResults);
      break;
  }
  break;
```

**Add case 'K' for kill feed (careful — 'K' already used for KD/KU key events):**
- Add inside existing case "K": `case "F":` handler for kill feed
```
case "F": // Kill feed: KF{killerId}|{killerNick}|{victimId}|{victimNick}
  var parts = received_msg.substring(2).split("|");
  var killEvent = { killerId: Number(parts[0]), killerNick: parts[1], victimId: Number(parts[2]), victimNick: parts[3], time: Date.now() };
  killFeed.push(killEvent);
  if (typeof HUD !== 'undefined') HUD.addKillFeedEntry(killEvent);
  // Also add to chat as kill-info
  addKillToChat(killEvent.killerNick, killEvent.victimNick);
  break;
```

**Add case 'S' for scoreboard (new top-level):**
```
case "S":
  switch (action) {
    case "B": // Scoreboard: SB{id}|{nick}|{kills}|{deaths};{id2}|...
      var entries = received_msg.substring(2).split(";");
      scoreboardData = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < entries.length; i++) {
        var p = entries[i].split("|");
        if (p.length >= 4) {
          scoreboardData.push({ id: Number(p[0]), nickname: p[1], kills: Number(p[2]), deaths: Number(p[3]) });
        }
      }
      if (typeof HUD !== 'undefined') HUD.updateScoreboard(scoreboardData);
      break;
  }
  break;
```

**Handle PK (player killed) — add inside existing case "P":**
```
case "K": // Player killed: PK{id}
  var id = Number(received_msg.substring(2));
  var player = world.getPlayer(id);
  if (player != null) {
    player.alive = false;
    player.remove();
  }
  break;
```

